obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (36525)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36525&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Illegal Migrants`
  line `(Determination by Tribunals) Act, 1983.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be deemed to have come into force in the State of Assam on the 15th day of October, 1983`
  line `and in any other State on such date as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazeette, appoint and different dates may be appointed for different States and references in this Act to`
  line `the commencement of this Act shall be construed in relation to any State as references to the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act in such State.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (36526)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Application.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36526&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall apply to or in relation to—`
  line
  line `(a) any person who was in any State and who had been expelled from that State or India before`
  line `the commencement of this Act in that State or in relation to whose expulsion from such State or India`
  line `any order made before such commencement under any other law is in force;`
  line
  line `(b) any person detected as a foreigner at the time of his entry across any border of India;`
  line
  line `(c) any foreigner who, having entered into India under a valid passport or travel document,`
  line `continued to remain therein after the expiry of the period for which he was authorised to remain in`
  line `India under such passport or travel document.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (36527)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Definitions and construction of references.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36527&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise`
  line requires,—
  line
  line `(a) "Appellate Tribunal" means an Appellate Tribunal established by the Central Government`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(b) "foreigner" has the same meaning as in the Foreigners Act, 1946 (31 of 1946);`
  line
  line `(c) "illegal migrant" means a person in respect of whom each of the following conditions is`
  line `satisfied, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) he has entered into India on or after the 25th day of March, 1971,`
  line
  line `(ii) he is a foreigner,`
  line
  line `(iii) he has entered into India without being in possession of a valid passport or other travel`
  line `document or any other lawful authority in that behalf;`
  line
  line `(d) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(e) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "Tribunal" means a Tribunal established by the Central Government under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 5.`
  line
  line `(2) Any reference in this Act to any law which is not in force in any area shall, in relation to that area,`
  line `be construed as a reference to the corresponding law, if any, in force in that area.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (36528)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Overriding effect of the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36528&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Act or of any rule or order made`
  line `thereunder shall have effect notwithstanding anything contained in the Passport (Entry into India) Act,`
  line `1920 (34 of 1920) or the Foreigners Act, 1946 (31 of 1946) or the Immigrants (Expulsion from Assam)`
  line `Act, 1950 (10 of 1950) or the Passports Act, 1967 (15 of 1967) or any rule or order made under any of the`
  line `said Acts and in force for the time being.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), nothing in`
  line `the proviso to section 2 of the Immigrants (Expulsion from Assam) Act, 1950 (10 of 1950) shall apply to`
  line `or in relation to an illegal migrant as defined in Clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (36529)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Establishment of Illegal Migrants (Determination) Tribunals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1988, s. 2, for "three members" (w.e.f. 25-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36529&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `may, by notification, establish, for the purposes of this Act, as many Illegal Migrants (Determination)`
  line `Tribunals as it may deem necessary and specify the principal place of sitting of, and the territorial limits`
  line `within which, each such Tribunal shall exercise its jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall be appointed as a member of any such Tribunal unless he is or has been a District`
  line `Judge or an Additional District Judge in any State.`
  line
  line `(3) Each Tribunal shall consist of ^1`
  line `[two members].`
  line
  line `(4) On the establishment of a Tribunal, the Central Government shall appoint one of the members`
  line `thereof as the Chairman of such Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(5) Each Tribunal shall sit in its principal place of sitting and in such other place or places as its`
  line `Chairman may, from time to time, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (36530)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Filling of vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "any other member" (w.e.f. 25-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36530&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `If, for any reason, any vacancy occurs in the office of the Chairman or`
  line ^1
  line `[the member] of a Tribunal, the Central Government may fill the vacancy by appointing any person who`
  line `fulfils the qualifications specified in sub-section (2) of section 5, as the Chairman, or, as the case may be,`
  line `member of such Tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (36531)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Staff of the Tribunals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36531&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall make available to every Tribunal such`
  line `staff as may be necessary for the discharge of its functions under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (36532)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `References or applications to Tribunals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36532&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any question arises as to whether any person is`
  line `or is not an illegal migrant, the Central Government may, whether such question has arisen on a`
  line `representation made by such person against any order under the Foreigners Act, 1946`
  line `(31 of 1946) requiring him not to remain in India or to any other effect or has arisen in any other manner`
  line `whatsoever, refer such question to a Tribunal for decision.`
  line
  line `(2)`
  line ^1
  line `*** any person may make an application to the Tribunal, for its decision, as to whether the`
  line `person whose name and other particulars are given in the application, is or is not an illegal migrant:`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[Provided that no such application shall be entertained by the Tribunal unless the person in relation`
  line `to whom the application is made is found, or resides, within the jurisdiction of the same police station`
  line `wherein the applicant has the place of residence.]`
  line
  line `(3) Every application made under sub-section (2) shall be made in such form and in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed and shall be accompanied by affidavits sworn by not less than ^3`
  line `[two persons residing`
  line `within the jurisdiction of the same police station] in which the person referred to in the application is`
  line `found, or residing, corroborating the averments made in the application, and shall also be accompanied by`
  line `such fee, being not less than ^4`
  line `[ten] and not more than one hundred, rupees, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line ^5
  line `[(4) Every reference under sub-section (1) shall be made to the Tribunal within the territorial limits`
  line `of whose jurisdiction the place of residence of the person named in such reference is, at the time of`
  line `making such reference, situated:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such person has no place of residence, the reference shall be made to the`
  line `Tribunal within the territorial limits of whose jurisdiction such person, is at the time of making such`
  line `reference, found.`
  line
  line `(5) Every application under sub-section (2) shall be made to the Tribunal within the territorial limits`
  line `of whose jurisdiction the person named in such application is found or, as the case may be, has his place`
  line `of residence, at the time of making such application.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words, brackets and figure "Without prejudice to the power conferred on the Central Government by sub-section (1)"`
  line `omitted by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 25-4-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for the proviso (w.e.f. 25-4-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 24 of 1988, s. 4, for "two persons residing within three kilometres of the area" (w.e.f. 25-4-1988).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "twenty-five" (w.e.f. 25-4-1988).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 25-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_a:
  sectionId (36533)
  sectionNo 8A
  orderNo 9
  title `Application to the Central Government for reference.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 25-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36533&sectionno=8A&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[8A. Application to the Central Government for reference.-- (1) Any person may make an`
  line `application to the Central Government, for decision by a Tribunal, as to whether the person whose name`
  line `and other particulars are given in the application, is or is not an illegal migrant, and where any such`
  line `application is received by the Central Government, it may, on the basis of any information in its`
  line `possession or after making such inquiry as it deems fit, reject the application on the ground that the`
  line `application is frivolous or vexatious or it does not comply with the requirements of this section or refer`
  line `such application to a Tribunal for decision.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application made under sub-section (1) shall be made in such form and in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed and shall be accompanied by a declaration by another person residing within the`
  line `jurisdiction of the same revenue sub-division in which the applicant resides in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed to the effect that the particulars mentioned in the application are true to his knowledge,`
  line `information and belief:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall make more than ten such applications or more than ten such`
  line declarations.
  line
  line `(3) Every reference under sub-section (1) shall be made to the Tribunal within the territorial limits of`
  line `whose jurisdiction the place of residence of the person named in such reference is, at the time of making`
  line `such reference, situated:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such person has no place of residence, the reference shall be made to the`
  line `Tribunal within the territorial limits of whose jurisdiction such person is, at the time of making such`
  line `reference, found.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (36534)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Powers of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36534&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Every Tribunal shall have the same powers as are vested in a civil court`
  line `under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit, in respect of the following`
  line `matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of witnesses and examining them on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) reception of evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning of public records from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing of any commission for the examination of witnesses.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (36535)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Procedure with respect to references under sub-section (1) of section 8.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. s. 6, ibid., for "section 8" (w.e.f. 25-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36535&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `On receipt of a`
  line `reference under sub-section (1) of ^1`
  line `[section 8 or sub-section (1) of section 8A] the Tribunal shall serve on`
  line `the person named in such reference, a notice, accompanied by a copy of such reference, calling upon him`
  line `to make, within a period of thirty days from the date of receipt of such notice, such representation with regard to the averments made in the reference, and to produce such evidence as he may think fit in`
  line `support of his defence:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Tribunal is satisfied that the person aforesaid was prevented by sufficient cause`
  line `from making his representation and from producing evidence in support of his defence within the said`
  line `period of thirty days, it may permit him to make his representation and to produce evidence in support of`
  line `his defence, within such further period, not exceeding thirty days, as it may, by order, specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (36536)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Procedure with respect to applications under sub-section (2) of section 8.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36536&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of`
  line `an application under sub-section (2) of section 8, the Tribunal shall issue a notice, accompanied by a copy`
  line `of the application, to the prescribed authority calling upon it to furnish, after making such inquiry as that`
  line `authority may deem fit, a report to the Tribunal with regard to the averments made in the application.`
  line
  line `(2) If, on a consideration of the report made by the prescribed authority, the Tribunal is satisfied`
  line that—
  line
  line `(a) the person named in the application is not an illegal migrant or that the application is frivolous`
  line `of vexatious, or has not been made in good faith, the Tribunal shall, after giving the applicant an`
  line `opportunity to be heard, reject the application;`
  line
  line `(b) there are reasonable grounds to believe that the person named in the application is an illegal`
  line `migrant, the Tribunal shall issue a notice accompanied by a copy of the application, to the person`
  line `named in the application, calling upon him to make, within thirty days from the date of receipt of the`
  line `notice, such representation with regard to the averments made in the application and to produce such`
  line `evidence as he may think fit in support of his defence:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Tribunal is satisfied that the person aforesaid was prevented by sufficient`
  line `cause from making his representation and from producing evidence in support of his defence within`
  line `the said period of thirty days, it may permit him to make his representation and to produce evidence`
  line `in support of his defence, within such further period, not exceeding thirty days, as it may, by order,`
  line specify.
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (36537)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Determination of the question as to whether a person is an illegal migrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36537&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tribunal`
  line `to which a reference has been made under ^1`
  line `[section 8 or section 8A, or to which an application has been`
  line `made under section 8], shall, after taking such evidence as may be adduced before it and after making`
  line `such inquiry as it may think fit and after hearing such persons as it may deem appropriate, by order,`
  line `decide the question as to whether the person named in such reference or application, as the case may be,`
  line `is or is not an illegal migrant:`
  line
  line `Provided that where for the determination of such question in any case the decision on any issue`
  line `renders any decision on any other issue or issues unnecessary, the Tribunal may not decide such other`
  line `issue or issues.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(2) Where the members of the Tribunal differ in their opinion on any point, the Chairman of the`
  line `Tribunal shall state the point or points on which they differ and make a reference to the President of the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal which exercises jurisdiction in relation to the Tribunal who shall refer the case for`
  line `hearing on such point or points by a member of another Tribunal under its jurisdiction and such point or`
  line `points shall be decided according to the opinion of that member and such decision shall be deemed to be`
  line `the decision of the Tribunal.]`
  line
  line `(3) The Tribunal shall send a copy of every order passed by it to the prescribed authority`
  line ^3
  line `[or authorities] and to the parties to the reference, or the application, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) Every order passed under sub-section (1) shall, subject to the decision of the Appellate Tribunal,`
  line `be final and shall not be called in question in any court.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1988, s. 7, for "section 8, or to which an application has been made under that section" (w.e.f. 25-4-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 25-4-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 25-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (36538)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Reference and application to be disposed of within six months.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "section 8 or application made to a Tribunal under that section" (w.e.f. 25-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36538&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Every reference made to a`
  line `Tribunal under ^1[section 8 or section 8A or application made to a Tribunal under section 8] shall be`
  line `inquired into as expeditiously as possible and every endeavour shall be made to conclude such inquiry within a period of six months from the date of the service, on the person concerned, of a copy of such`
  line `reference or application.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (36539)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 24 of 1988, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36539&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government, or any person, named in a reference or an application under`
  line `section 8, or any applicant under sub-section (2) of that section ^1`
  line `[or any person named in a reference`
  line `under section 8A] may, if it or he is not satisfied with any order made by a Tribunal under section 12,`
  line `prefer an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal against such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (36540)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36540&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, establish for each State`
  line `in which this Act is in force an Appellate Tribunal to be known as the Illegal Migrants (Determination)`
  line `Appellate Tribunal for deciding appeals preferred under section 14 against orders made by Tribunals in`
  line `the State and specify the principal place of sitting of such Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall be appointed as a member of an Appellate Tribunal unless he is or has been a`
  line `Judge of a High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) An Appellate Tribunal shall consist of as many members, not being ^1`
  line `[less than two] and more`
  line `than six, as the Central Government may think fit.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall appoint one of the members of an Appellate Tribunal to be the`
  line `President thereof.`
  line
  line `(5) An Appellate Tribunal shall sit in its principal place of sitting or any such other place or places as`
  line `the President thereof may, from time to time, appoint.`
  line
  line `(6) The powers and functions of an Appellate Tribunal may be exercised and discharged by benches`
  line `constituted by the President thereof from amongst the members thereof ^2`
  line `[which may either be single`
  line `member benches or benches consisting of not less than two members.]`
  line
  line `(7) The Central Government shall make available to every Appellate Tribunal such staff as may be`
  line `necessary for the discharge of its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(8) Every memorandum of appeal to an Appellate Tribunal shall be made in such form and in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed, and, in the case of an appeal preferred by an applicant under sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 8, shall also be accompanied by such fee, not being less than twenty-five and more than one`
  line `hundred rupees, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(9) Every appeal shall be preferred within thirty days from the date on which the order sought to be`
  line `appealed against was communicated to the appellant:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by`
  line `sufficient cause from preferring the appeal within the said period, admit an appeal after the expiry of the`
  line `aforesaid period of thirty days.`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(10) Every Appellate Tribunal shall have the same powers as are vested in an appellate court under`
  line `the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while hearing an appeal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 10, bid., for "less than three" (w.e.f. 25-4-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for "and each bench shall consist of not less than two members" (w.e.f. 25-4-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for sub-section (10) (w.e.f. 25-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (36541)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Order of the Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36541&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appellate Tribunal may, after giving the parties to`
  line `the appeal a reasonable opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it may think fit,`
  line `confirming, modifying or annulling the order appealed against or may remand the case to the Tribunal`
  line `which had passed such order with such directions to that Tribunal as the Appellate Tribunal may think fit,`
  line `for fresh determination after taking additional evidence, if necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an appeal had been heard by the Appellate Tribunal and the members thereof differ in their`
  line `opinion on any point, the decision on such point shall, where there is a majority, be according to the`
  line `opinion of such majority, and where there is no majority and the members are equally divided in their`
  line `opinion, they shall draw up a statement of the facts of the case and the point or points on which they differ`
  line `in their opinion and make a reference of the point or points or of the appeal, as the case may be, to the`
  line `President of such Tribunal, and on receipt of such reference, the President of the Tribunal shall arrange`
  line `for the hearing of such point or points, or the appeal, by one or more of the members of the Appellate Tribunal, and such point or points, or the appeal, as the case may be, shall be decided according to the`
  line `opinion of the majority of the members of the Appellate Tribunal, who have heard the appeal, including`
  line `those who had first heard it.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(3) The Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order passed by it under sub-section (1) to the`
  line `parties to the appeal, to the Tribunal concerned and to the prescribed authority or authorities.]`
  line
  line `(4)`
  line ^2
  line `*** every order passed under sub-section (1), other than an order remanding the case, shall be`
  line `final and no order passed under that sub-section shall be called in question in any court.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1988, s. 11, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 25-4-1988).`
  line `2. The words and figures "Subject to the provisions of section 17" omitted by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 24-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (36542)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power of superintendence by Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for section 17 (w.e.f. 24-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36542&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `^1[17. Power of superintendence by Appellate Tribunal.-- (1) Every Appellate Tribunal shall have`
  line `superintendence over all the Tribunals in the State.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provisions, the Appellate Tribunal may--`
  line
  line `(a) call for returns from any Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(b) make general rules and specify forms for regulating the practice and proceedings of`
  line `Tribunals; and`
  line
  line `(c) specify the forms in which books, entries and accounts shall be kept by the officers of`
  line Tribunals.]
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (36543)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title Procedure.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36543&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder, every Tribunal`
  line `and every Appellate Tribunal shall have the power to regulate its own procedure in all matters arising out`
  line `of the exercise of its powers or for the discharge of its functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (36544)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Proceeding before every Tribunal to be judicial proceeding for certain purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36544&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line Every
  line `proceeding before a Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within`
  line `the meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purposes of section 196 of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860); and every such Tribunal or Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be, shall be deemed to a`
  line `civil court for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (36545)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title `Expulsion of illegal migrants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36545&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Where a person has been determined by a Tribunal, or, as`
  line `the case may be, by the Appellate Tribunal, to be an illegal migrant, the Central Government shall, by`
  line `order served on such person, direct such person to remove himself from India within such time and by`
  line `such route as may be specified in the order and may give such further directions in regard to his removal`
  line `from India as it may consider necessary or expedient.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) Any police officer not below the rank of a Superintendent of Police shall have such powers as`
  line `may be necessary, including the power to obtain a bond from any person for the due compliance of an`
  line `order under sub-section (1) and to arrest such person in the event of his failure to furnish such bond to the`
  line `satisfaction of such police officer.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. S. 20 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 24-4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 24-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (36546)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36546&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification, direct that the powers and`
  line `duties conferred or imposed on it by this Act, other than the powers conferred by section 28, and the`
  line `powers conferred by this section, may, subject to such conditions as may be specified in the notification,`
  line `be exercised or discharged also by—`
  line
  line `(a) any officer subordinate to the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) any State Government or any officer subordinate to that Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21_a:
  sectionId (36547)
  sectionNo 21A
  orderNo 23
  title `Power to bind certain persons against whom complaint is made under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 24 of 1988, s. 14 (w.e.f. 24-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36547&sectionno=21A&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[21A. Power to bind certain persons against whom complaint is made under the`
  line `Act.-- Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, it shall be lawful`
  line `for a police officer not below the rank of a Superintendent of Police, if he is satisfied that the`
  line `circumstances so require and for reasons to be recorded in writing, to direct any person against whom a`
  line `reference or an application has been made under this Act to enter into a bond with or without sureties for`
  line `making himself available for the inquiry and observance of such restrictions or conditions as may be`
  line `specified by such police officer:`
  line
  line `Provided that if such person fails to enter into such bond he may be arrested and detained in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (36548)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 24
  title `Power to give effect to the orders, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36548&sectionno=22&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Any authority empowered by or in pursuance of the`
  line `provisions of this Act to exercise any power, may, in addition to any other action expressly provided for`
  line `in this Act, take, or cause to be taken, such steps, and use, or cause to be used, such force, as may in its`
  line `opinion be reasonably necessary for the effective exercise of such power.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (36549)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 25
  title `Bar of jurisdiction of civil courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36549&sectionno=23&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Where a Tribunal or Appellate Tribunal has been`
  line `established for any area for the purpose of determining whether a person is or is not an illegal migrant, no`
  line `civil court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any question relating to that matter in that area and no`
  line `injunction or any other order in respect of any action taken by, or before, the Tribunal or Appellate`
  line `Tribunal in respect of that matter shall be granted or made by any civil court.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (36550)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 26
  title `Transitory provision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36550&sectionno=24&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Where in any suit or other legal proceeding pending, whether in a civil`
  line `court or in any Tribunal established under any other law for the time being in force, immediately before`
  line `the commencement of this Act, a question arises as to whether a person is or is not an illegal migrant,`
  line `such court or Tribunal shall, without deciding such question, make an order transferring such suit or other`
  line `legal proceeding to the Tribunal under this Act within the territorial limits of whose jurisdiction such`
  line `court or other Tribunal is situate and on such transfer such question shall be dealt with by such Tribunal`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (36551)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 27
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 24-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36551&sectionno=25&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Any person who,—`
  line
  line `(a) contravenes or attempts to contravene, or abets the contravention of, any order made under`
  line `section 20; or`
  line
  line `(b) fails to comply with any direction given by any such order; or`
  line
  line `(c) harbours any person who has contravened any order made under section 20 or has failed to`
  line `comply with any direction given by any such order,`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one year but which may`
  line `extend to three years and with fine which shall not be less than two thousand rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for adequate and special reasons to be mentioned in the judgment,`
  line `impose a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than one year or a fine of less than two thousand`
  line rupees.]
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (36552)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 28
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36552&sectionno=26&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against any person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (36553)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36553&sectionno=27&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order to be published in the Official Gazette, make such`
  line `provisions, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for`
  line `removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House or Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (36554)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36554&sectionno=28&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules to carry`
  line `out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the form and the manner in which an application may be made and the fee which shall`
  line `accompany such application, as required by sub-section (3) of section 8;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(aa) the form and the manner in which an application, and the form in which a declaration, may`
  line `be made under sub-section (2) of section 8A;]`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(b) the authority or authorities to be prescribed under sections 11, 12 and 16;]`
  line
  line `(c) the form and the manner in which an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal may be preferred and`
  line `the fee which shall accompany such appeal as required by sub-section (8) of section 15;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(ca) the manner of arrest and detention under the proviso to section 21A;]`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 24 of 1988, s. 16 (w.e.f. 24-4-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for clause (b) (w.e.f. 24-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (36555)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 31
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421&sectionId=36555&sectionno=29&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00021_198339_1517807325421
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Illegal Migrants (Determination by Tribunals) Ordinance, 1983`
  line `(8 of 1983), is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
